@@eThe Great Northern Forest@@N

  Four hundred square miles of unbroken canopy stretch between
@@yMidgaard@@N to the south and @@yKowloon@@N to the north. Neither city
claims the forest as sole territory, yet both govern it through a
shared charter forged at a neutral glade called @@eThe Oath-Crossing@@N.

  The @@yLantern Road@@N threads through its heart -- not a king's road,
but a negotiated one. Its architect, Ilren Voss, followed game trails
and dry streambeds rather than forcing a straight line through living
woodland. Lantern posts mark every bend and ford, bearing both
Midgaard runes and northern knot-signs.

  Five zones define the forest's character. The @@gSouthern Verge@@N is
sunlit broadleaf under Midgaard's road wardens. The @@gMosswater Bends@@N
are treacherous fenlands where mire-clans trade resin and fish oil
from reed platforms. The @@gIronpine Rise@@N climbs sharply into granite
ridges and ancient conifers so dense they dull axes. The @@dAncestor
Deeps@@N glow with luminescent moss beneath a canopy that blocks all
sun, where standing stones mark the Cairn-Keepers' old tribunal sites.
The @@gNorthern Crown@@N thins near Kowloon's approach, patrolled by the
Wardens of Iron on seasonal rotation.

  Hidden peoples dwell beneath the boughs. @@eRoadwardens@@N and lamp-keepers
maintain the route under joint commission. @@eMire-clans@@N trade bark and
medicine from the fens. @@eStone-antler circles@@N guard megalith rings older
than either city. @@rAshfang warbands@@N raid from the far interior, their
teeth blackened with ash. @@rRootbound cultists@@N sabotage road infrastructure,
believing the forest is a sleeping deity and the Lantern Road a wound.

  Two centuries ago, the @@dAsh Winters@@N -- volcanic fallout from distant
Cinderteeth eruptions -- poisoned streams and killed a third of the
forest's game. Hunger turned territorial disputes into ambush wars.
The crisis forged the @@yPassage Tithe@@N system: caravans paying in grain,
salt, and iron nails rather than coin, stabilizing waystations that
endure to this day.

  The @@yNorthern Covenant@@N governs all: no army may march the road in
war formation, timbering is restricted to safety cuts, shrine groves
and burial mounds are inviolable. A fifth article requires all
northern-bound manifests to carry dual marks -- Midgaard wax and
Kowloon thread-knot. The forest endures as a diplomatic buffer where
pragmatism meets covenant law.
